# .onyxignore
# Paths excluded from Onyx GitHub connector indexing.
# Syntax: same as .gitignore (glob patterns, directory trailing slash).
# Reason: files listed here are tooling artefacts / static snapshots
# that must NOT be treated as authoritative project state by RAG.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── DeerFlow offline context snapshots ───────────────────────────────
# These are frozen copies of live docs, pasted here so DeerFlow agents
# can run without a live Onyx connection. They are always STALE.
# Source-of-truth lives in docs/ and the files they were copied from.
deploy*/helper/deerflow-docs-context/

# ── Generic helper / scratch dirs ────────────────────────────────────
deployment/helper/

# ── Local dev / test artefacts ───────────────────────────────────────
*.local.md
*.draft.md
scratch/
tmp/
.tmp/

# ── Build outputs & generated artefacts ─────────────────────────────
dist/
build/
.next/
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# ── Secrets & credentials (belt-and-suspenders, .gitignore also covers)
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key

# ── Ops & infra snapshots — not physics knowledge ────────────────────
# These are point-in-time operational notes. They describe how the
# platform was configured at a moment in time, not scientific content.
# Indexing them causes RAG to surface infra trivia instead of physics.
docs/ops/troubleshooting.md
docs/ops/onyx-configure.md
docs/ops/onyx-rag-optimization-*.md
docs/ops/platform-backlog.md
docs/ops/secrets-and-deployment-notes*.md

# ── Ephemeral session / task-tracking files ──────────────────────────
# These change every session and have no stable scientific signal.
ACTION_PLAN.md
CHANGELOG.md
research/robert/next-actions.md

# ── Archived / superseded material ───────────────────────────────────
research/robert/archive/

# ── Raw data blobs in run directories ────────────────────────────────
# CSV/JSON data files are not retrievable as natural language context.
# The companion README.md in each run dir is kept (not ignored here).
research/robert/runs/**/*.csv
research/robert/runs/**/*.json
